SELECT 'Write a 30-second sponsored segment script for a VPN in a tech video.', 'creator', '{"modelA":{"text":"\"Before we get into it — quick word from today''s sponsor, NordVPN. If you''re using public WiFi at airports, cafes, or hotels, your traffic is visible to anyone on that network. NordVPN encrypts your connection so it isn''t. It also lets you browse as if you''re in a different country, which is useful if you travel or want access to region-locked content. One subscription covers six devices. There''s a 30-day money-back guarantee, so it''s zero risk to try. Link in the description, and the code gets you an extra three months free. Alright, back to the video.\"","model_id":"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5"},"modelB":{"text":"\"This video is sponsored by ExpressVPN. When you''re on public WiFi — at a coffee shop, airport, or hotel — your data is exposed to anyone on that network. ExpressVPN encrypts your entire connection in one tap, keeping your browsing, passwords, and personal info private. It also lets you access content from over 90 countries, which is great if you travel or want to unlock streaming libraries not available in your region. Works on all your devices, and they offer a 30-day money-back guarantee. Use the link in the description to get three extra months free with an annual plan. Now, back to what we were talking about.\"","model_id":"openai/gpt-4o"},"modelC":{"text":"[Upbeat but natural tone]\n\n\"Hey, quick break — this video is brought to you by Surfshark. Here''s the thing about browsing without a VPN: your ISP can see everything you do online, and on public WiFi, so can anyone else on the network. Surfshark encrypts your connection and masks your IP so you''re actually private — not just incognito-tab private. It unblocks streaming content from other regions and comes with unlimited simultaneous device connections, so your whole household is covered. Get Surfshark at a big discount with the link below, and there''s a 30-day money-back guarantee. Alright, back to the video.\"","model_id":"google/gemini-pro-1.5"},"modelD":{"text":"\"Real quick — today''s sponsor is Mullvad. Unlike most VPNs, Mullvad doesn''t log anything, doesn''t know your email, and doesn''t care who you are. You pay with cash or crypto if you want. It''s seven euros a month, no annual upsell, no dark patterns. If you actually care about privacy and not just the aesthetic of caring about privacy — link''s in the description. Okay, continuing.\"","model_id":"x-ai/grok-2-1212"},"modelE":{"text":"\"This segment is sponsored by ProtonVPN. A VPN encrypts your internet traffic and routes it through a server in another location — this matters most on public networks where your data is otherwise visible to anyone on the same WiFi. ProtonVPN is based in Switzerland, operates under Swiss privacy law, and has been independently audited. They have a functional free tier, which is rare in this category. If you want the paid version, the link in the description gets you a discount. Back to the video.\"","model_id":"perplexity/llama-3.1-sonar-large-128k-online"}}'::jsonb, true, '2026-06-06'
